article.headline: Quinnipiac 70, St. Francis, NY 44
article.story: NEW YORK -- Justin Rutty scored 20 points and James Feldeine had 17 to help Quinnipiac College defeat St. Francis, N.Y., 70-44 Thursday night. James Johnson added 13 points and Louis Brookins had 11 rebounds for the Bobcats (8-8, 4-2 Northeast Conference), who led 29-19 at the half. Ricky Cadell had 20 points and John Gooden scored eight for the Terriers (4-12, 2-4). Cadell's 3-pointer got St. Francis within 18-16 with 4:46 left in the first half, but Quinnipiac took control with an 11-3 run to close out the half.
